# dfmt:v1 begin
# Context Discipline
#
# This project uses DFMT. Prefer the dfmt_* MCP tools over native
# Bash, Read, WebFetch, Glob, Grep. Always include an `intent`
# argument describing what you need from the output.
#
# Call dfmt_remember to record user decisions so they survive context
# compaction. On any dfmt_* failure, report it (one line) and then fall
# back to the native tool — the ban is on *silent* fallback, not on
# fallback itself. If the native tool is also denied, stop and ask the
# user.
#
# See full rules in AGENTS.md.
# dfmt:v1 end
